Step 1. Go To Datadog And Create The Account

Go To Datadog https://ap1.datadoghq.com/ -> Click On Try for free -> Select a Region(ðŸ‡¯ðŸ‡µ Japan (AP1) -> Business Email -> Full Name -> Company -> Password -> 
Sign Up -> Copy And Paste The 8-Digit Datadog Verification Code From Gmail In Spam -> Next -> Now Run The URL https://ap1.datadoghq.com/ 



Step 2. Copy The Datadog API Key

Datadog Console -> Ctrl + K -> Search API Keys -> Click On API Keys -> Copy The API Key



Step 3. Install The Datadog agent

DD_API_KEY=YOUR_DATADOG_API_KEY \
DD_SITE="ap1.datadoghq.com" \
DD_AGENT_MAJOR_VERSION=7 \
bash -c "$(curl -L https://s3.amazonaws.com/dd-agent/scripts/install_script.sh)"



Step 4.  Enable The Logs in File datadog.yaml

grep -q "^logs_enabled" /etc/datadog-agent/datadog.yaml && \
sed -i 's/^#\?\s*logs_enabled:.*/logs_enabled: true/' /etc/datadog-agent/datadog.yaml || \
echo "logs_enabled: true" >> /etc/datadog-agent/datadog.yaml



Step 5. Restart Of The Datadog Agent

systemctl restart datadog-agent



Step 6. Check The Status Of The Datadog Agent

systemctl status datadog-agent
